    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Published in 1776, &amp;ldquo;The Wealth of Nations&amp;rdquo; is a foundational text in economics, written by Scottish philosopher and economist Adam Smith. The book is considered one of the most influential works on economics and politics in the history of ideas.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
